我烦透了。

171
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:11,600
Katrina I'm sick and tired of all of your whining.
Katrina 我烦透了你的抱怨。

172
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:13,640
Go do the dishes and don't complain.
去洗碗，别抱怨了。

173
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:14,640
Charles Right.
Charles 对。

174
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:16,160
So it's always, it always goes together.
所以它总是连在一起用。

175
00:07:16,160 --> 00:07:17,640
You are sick and tired.
你烦透了。

176
00:07:17,640 --> 00:07:18,640
Katrina Right.
Katrina 对。

177
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:19,640
And sick comes first.
而且“烦”在前面。

178
00:07:19,640 --> 00:07:20,640
So I'm sick and tired of this.
所以我烦透了这件事。

179
00:07:20,640 --> 00:07:22,800
I'm sick and tired of your bad attitude.
我烦透了你的坏态度。

180
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:23,800
Charles Okay.
Charles 好的。

181
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:25,200
So and that means that you are...
所以这意味着你……

182
00:07:25,200 --> 00:07:26,760
Katrina I'm just tired of it.
Katrina 我就是厌倦了。

183
00:07:26,760 --> 00:07:29,040
I don't want you to have a bad attitude anymore.
我不想你再有坏态度了。

184
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:30,040
I'm just, yeah.
我就是，嗯。

185
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:31,280
Charles I'm really annoyed by it.
Charles 我对此很恼火。

186
00:07:31,280 --> 00:07:32,280
I'm annoyed.
我很恼火。

187
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:33,280
Okay.
好的。

188
00:07:33,280 --> 00:07:34,280
Sick and tired.
烦透了。

189
00:07:34,280 --> 00:07:35,680
And then we saw a phrase that was a little bit separated.
然后我们看到一个稍微分开的短语。

190
00:07:35,680 --> 00:07:37,800
He said the sentence went like this.
他说句子是这样的。

191
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:42,520
His work turned thousands of years of ideas about creation on their head.
他的工作颠覆了数千年来关于创造的观点。

192
00:07:42,520 --> 00:07:44,320
So to turn something on its head.
所以“彻底颠覆某事物”。

193
00:07:44,320 --> 00:07:46,000
Katrina Like you said, Marco, it's split into two
Katrina 就像你说的，Marco，它分成两

194
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,000
parts.
部分。

195
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:50,280
So he turned the field of computer science on its head.
所以他彻底颠覆了计算机科学领域。

196
00:07:50,280 --> 00:07:55,760
So to turn on its head means to completely reverse something, to turn it around.
所以“彻底颠覆”意思是完全反转某事物，把它翻过来。

197
00:07:55,760 --> 00:07:58,120
You think 180 degrees.
你想成180度。

198
00:07:58,120 --> 00:08:03,760
And so if biology used to be one way, then Darwin made it completely different.
所以如果生物学以前是一种方式，那么达尔文让它完全改变了。

199
00:08:03,760 --> 00:08:05,840
Charles So we can say that Isaac Newton completely
Charles 所以我们可以说艾萨克·牛顿彻底

200
00:08:05,840 --> 00:08:10,160
turned physics on its head with his theory or his findings on gravity.
用他的引力理论或发现颠覆了物理学。

201
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:13,600
Katrina And then years and years later, we had Albert
卡特里娜 然后过了很多很多年，我们有了阿尔伯特。

202
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:18,840
Einstein who turned those theories or who turned that theory on its head with his own
爱因斯坦，他用自己的理论彻底颠覆了那些理论。

203
00:08:18,840 --> 00:08:19,840
ideas about physics.
关于物理学的想法。

204
00:08:19,840 --> 00:08:20,840
Charles Very good.
查尔斯 非常好。

205
00:08:20,840 --> 00:08:25,880
So to turn something on its head, to completely change the course of or prove something to
所以，要让某件事彻底颠覆，完全改变方向，或者证明某事是错的。

206
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:27,880
be maybe wrong.
可能是错的。

207
00:08:27,880 --> 00:08:32,760
And the last phrase that we have is the person argued that Darwin's theories were full of
我们最后一个短语是，那个人声称达尔文的理论充满了

208
00:08:32,760 --> 00:08:33,760
holes.
洞。

209
00:08:33,760 --> 00:08:34,760
Katrina Okay.
卡特里娜 好的。

210
00:08:34,760 --> 00:08:36,480
So to say a theory is full of holes is a little bit
所以说一个理论漏洞百出，有点……

