所以也许你会说，好吧，厨房里的饼干没了，Marco。

218
00:08:57,500 --> 00:08:58,940
And I saw you in the kitchen.
我在厨房里看到你了。

219
00:08:58,940 --> 00:09:00,880
So clearly you ate the cookies.
所以你显然吃了饼干。

220
00:09:00,880 --> 00:09:01,880
Charles Right.
查尔斯说得对。

221
00:09:01,880 --> 00:09:05,080
So I can say that's full of holes because it was me and it was three other people who
所以我可以这么说，那全是漏洞，因为当时是我和其他三个人一起。

222
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:06,080
were in the kitchen.
我们在厨房里。

223
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:07,080
So you can't blame me.
所以你不能怪我。

224
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:08,080
Katrina Ah, it could have been the other two people.
卡特里娜 啊，可能是另外两个人。

225
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:09,080
Charles Right.
查尔斯说得对。

226
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:13,440
So if something is full of holes, it's that it has maybe mistakes or it's still missing
所以如果某件事“漏洞百出”，那意味着它可能有很多错误，或者还有缺失。

227
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:15,120
complete evidence to prove it right.
完整的证据来证明它是正确的。

228
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:16,520
Katrina Or it has bad logic.
Katrina 或者它的逻辑有问题。

229
00:09:16,520 --> 00:09:17,520
Charles Bad logic.
查尔斯，逻辑不通。

230
00:09:17,520 --> 00:09:18,520
All right.
好的。

231
00:09:18,520 --> 00:09:19,520
Interesting.
有意思。

232
00:09:19,520 --> 00:09:23,000
So we've taken a look at a lot of words and different phrases here.
所以我们在这里看了很多单词和不同的短语。

